            <div type="edition">
                <ab><persName><name key="Αἰνέας">Αἰνέας</name></persName> <name key="Πάν" type="divine">Πανὶ</name>.</ab></div>
            
            <div type="translation">
            <p>Aeneas (dedicated this) to Pan.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>The item is part of a well-known class of Arcadian bronze statuettes dated to the
                    sixth century BCE. They represent local shepherds and served as dedications to
                    Pan at sanctuaries. Aeneas as an Arcadian name is attested in Pindar (O. 6.88)
                    and Xenophon (An. 4, 7, 13; Hell. 7.3). </p></div>
            
